{
  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, A max ðδÞ reaches its minimum value when δ ≈ 0.3, consistent with the fact that ΔD eff reaches its minimum at δ ≈ 0.3.",
    "Moreover, ΔD eff (δ) is highly correlated with the geometric parameter A max ðδÞ (Fig. 9j), highlighting that the differentiation effect of the obstacle lattice on oppositely handed CAPs, a physical effect, can be quantitatively estimated by the degree of the asymmetry of the lattice, a pure geometric characteristic.",
    "Our simulations show the novel behavior of individual CAPs in the lattices of circular disk obstacles under three cases.",
    "The key results are confirmed by granular experiments.",
    "Case (1) is about CAP diffusion in the square and triangular lattices."
  ]
}